text: (home in Aymara) is a city in Chile. It is in the province of Tamarugal, region of Tarapacá. It had 1.275 people as of 2002. It was founded in September 8, 1970. It has an area of 2.200,2 km². The slogan of the city is effort land. Category:Cities in Chile Category:Tamarugal Province
title: Camiña
